    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Windsor armchairs with a low back that terminates at arm level and usually is comprised of a three-piece sawn arm rail that follows the outside curve of the seat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000014271/Evans, American Windsor Furniture (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sillones Windsor con un respaldo bajo que termina a nivel del brazo y normalmente comprende una baranda de brazo aserrada de tres piezas que sigue la curva exterior del asiento.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
